Package: rtpaudio-clients
Architecture: any
Depends: libaudiocommon0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libaudiodecoder0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libaudiowriter0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         librtpaudioclient0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libtdtoolbox0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: iputils-ping,
            iputils-tracepath,
            netperfmeter,
            rsplib-tools,
            subnetcalc,
            traceroute
Description: RTP Audio clients
 The RTP Audio system is a network sound streaming system. It has been
 designed for QoS performance analysis and teaching purposes.
 RTP Audio supports IPv4 and IPv6 including flowlabels and traffic
 classes, QoS management as well as transport via UDP and SCTP.
 .
 This package provides the RTP Audio clients.

Package: rtpaudio-server
Architecture: any
Depends: libqosmgr0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         librtpaudioserver0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         librtpserver0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libtdtoolbox0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: iputils-ping,
            iputils-tracepath,
            netperfmeter,
            rsplib-tools,
            subnetcalc,
            traceroute
Description: RTP Audio server
 The RTP Audio system is a network sound streaming system. It has been
 designed for QoS performance analysis and teaching purposes.
 RTP Audio supports IPv4 and IPv6 including flowlabels and traffic
 classes, QoS management as well as transport via UDP and SCTP.
 .
 This package provides the RTP Audio server.

Package: rtpaudio-all
Architecture: any
Depends: rtpaudio-clients (= ${binary:Version}),
         rtpaudio-server (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: RTP Audio sound streaming system
 The RTP Audio system is a network sound streaming system. It has been
 designed for QoS performance analysis and teaching purposes.
 RTP Audio supports IPv4 and IPv6 including flowlabels and traffic
 classes, QoS management as well as transport via UDP and SCTP.
